The Bank Management System provides complete control over the management of bank accounts through a graphical interface. The application directly connects to a MySQL database to perform Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) operations on customer and transaction records.

⚙️ Core Functionalities

Account Management

Create new customer accounts by specifying Account ID, Name, Type, Initial Balance, and Status.

Update account details such as type and status.

Delete inactive or unwanted accounts.

Transaction Management

Perform deposits, withdrawals, and inter-account transfers.

Maintain transaction history for each account automatically.

Prevent transactions on closed accounts or accounts with insufficient funds.

Data Management

Store all records securely in a MySQL database.

Automatically create required tables (Accounts, Transactions, Users) if they do not exist.

Include an administrator account (default username: Hritik, password: 260604).

Reporting and Export

View all accounts and their current balances.

Double-click any account to view its detailed transaction history.

Export account data to a CSV file for record-keeping or auditing.

Graphical User Interface (GUI)

Built using Tkinter for simplicity and responsiveness.

Navigation via buttons for each operation (Create, Deposit, Withdraw, Transfer, Change Status, Delete, Export, Refresh).

Clear data tables (Treeviews) to display accounts and transactions neatly.
